column1: * For model year 2015, manufacturers are using an improved testing procedure to determine the fuel consumption ratings of new light-duty vehicles. The Government of Canada-approved new test methods are more representative of typical driving conditions

and styles. The new test methods (5-cycle testing) supplement the standard (2-cycle) city and highway tests by integrating three additional test cycles that account for air conditioner use, cold temperature operation and driving at higher speeds with more
rapid acceleration and braking. The new 5-cycle testing results in higher fuel consumption ratings that are more representative of a vehicles on-road fuel consumption compared to the old ratings.

column2: City and highway fuel consumption ratings are shown in litres per 100 kilometres (L/100 km) - the combined rating (55% city, 45% hwy) is shown in L/100 km and in miles per imperial gallon (mpg)
Estimated tailpipe carbon dioxide emissions (in grams per kilometre) are based on fuel type and the combined fuel consumption rating.
